<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="710" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,243,975,999]" box="[144,243,975,999]" pageId="13" pageNumber="710">
<emphasis box="[144,243,975,999]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="710">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[144,1104,1015,1264]" pageId="13" pageNumber="710">
Most authors have followed 
<bibRefCitation author="Powell AWB" box="[483,634,1015,1039]" pageId="13" pageNumber="710" pagination="227 - 346" refId="ref21323" refString="Powell AWB. 1964. The family Turrridae in the Indo-Pacific. Part 1. The subfamily Turrinae. Indo-Pacific Moll. 1 (5): 227 - 346." type="journal article" year="1964">Powell (1964</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Powell AWB" box="[649,704,1015,1039]" pageId="13" pageNumber="710" pagination="1 - 184" refId="ref21354" refString="Powell AWB. 1966. The molluscan families Speightiidae and Turridae. Bull Auckland Inst Mus. 5: 1 - 184, 23 plates." type="book chapter" year="1966">1966</bibRefCitation>
) in preferring the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Iredale, 1931" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1931" class="Gastropoda" family="Pseudomelatomidae" genus="Epidirona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="710" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[995,1104,1015,1039]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="710">Epidirona</emphasis>
Iredale, 1931
</taxonomicName>
, to the earlier 
<taxonomicName authority="Hedley, 1918" authorityName="Hedley" authorityYear="1918" box="[459,711,1047,1071]" class="Gastropoda" family="Horaiclavidae" genus="Epideira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="710" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[459,553,1047,1071]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="710">Epideira</emphasis>
Hedley, 1918
</taxonomicName>
, as he regarded the 
<typeStatus box="[939,988,1048,1072]" pageId="13" pageNumber="710">type</typeStatus>
species of the latter genus as “indeterminate”. However, in the 
<typeStatus box="[744,793,1080,1104]" pageId="13" pageNumber="710">type</typeStatus>
collection of the BMNH is a specimen from the Gray collection labelled 
<taxonomicName authority="Reeve, 1843" authorityName="Reeve" authorityYear="1843" box="[666,1023,1111,1135]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Pleurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="710" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="owenii">
<emphasis box="[666,875,1111,1135]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="710">Pleurotoma owenii</emphasis>
Reeve, 1843
</taxonomicName>
, which 
<bibRefCitation author="Watson RB" box="[144,365,1143,1167]" pageId="13" pageNumber="710" pagination="1 - 756" refId="ref22109" refString="Watson RB. 1886. Reports on the Scaphopoda and Gastropoda collected by HMS Challenger during the years 1873 - 76. Challenger Rep Zool. 15: 1 - 756." type="journal article" year="1886">Watson (1886: 312)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hedley C" box="[424,638,1143,1167]" pageId="13" pageNumber="710" pagination="213 - 259" refId="ref20510" refString="Hedley C. 1922. A revision of the Australian Turridae. Rec Austr Mus. 13 (6): 213 - 259." type="journal article" year="1922">Hedley (1922: 230)</bibRefCitation>
regarded as a synonym of 
<bibRefCitation author="Gray JE" box="[949,1104,1143,1167]" pageId="13" pageNumber="710" pagination="474 - 496" refId="ref20206" refString="Gray JE. 1826. Mollusca. Appendix. In: King PP, editor. Narrative of a Survey of the Intertropical and Western Coasts of Australia, Performed Between the Years 1818 and 1822. Vol. 2. London: John Murray. p. 474 - 496." type="book chapter" year="1826">Gray’s (1826)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1826" box="[144,331,1175,1199]" class="Gastropoda" family="Clavatulidae" genus="Clavatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="710" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis box="[144,331,1175,1199]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="710">Clavatula striata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. There is even a possibility that it was based on the same specimen. Although 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1826" box="[258,363,1207,1231]" class="Gastropoda" family="Clavatulidae" genus="Clavatula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="710" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis box="[258,363,1207,1231]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="710">C. striata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not subsequently been recognised, it appears to be congeneric with 
<taxonomicName authority="Iredale, 1931" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1931" box="[200,550,1239,1263]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pseudomelatomidae" genus="Epidirona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="710" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hedleyi">
<emphasis box="[200,394,1239,1263]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="710">Epidirona hedleyi</emphasis>
Iredale, 1931
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[603,652,1240,1264]" pageId="13" pageNumber="710">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1931" box="[772,881,1239,1263]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pseudomelatomidae" genus="Epidirona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="710" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[772,881,1239,1263]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="710">Epidirona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
